results.title: Schism
results.description: The X-Treme team and the White Queen invade the danger room to face down Bogan and his Hellfire cronies who are holding Xavier's students captive; After Bogan is defeated, Xavier agrees to harbor Jeffrey at the Mansion; This decision leaves Storm (who thinks the young boy should face justice for the murders he committed) at odds with Prof X's ideals and the X-Treme team leave the X-Men once again.

results.title: Prodigal
results.description: Sam helps ease a crisis situation begun by a rampaging mutant and decides to join Storm and the X-Treme team.

results.title: God Loves, Man Kills II Part 1
results.description: The X-Men are vacationing in Kentucky when they get word that the prison plane carrying Reverend William Stryker has gone down killing everyone on board and someone is blaming the X-Men for the deed; In reality, Lady Deathstrike rescues Stryker and fakes the crash to implicate the X-Men; During their investigation, the Team X-Treme is taken down by a group of well armed mystery men; Stryker and Deathstrike show up in Chicago to kidnap Kitty Pryde.

results.description: The X-Men take down a group of soldiers sent to capture them and find out a little of Stryker's plan; Stryker and Deathstrike try to program Kitty's mind but find her defenses are too strong; While gathering information, Deathstrike's body is taken over by a mysterious presence and begins to kill Stryker's men.

results.description: The X-Men have to deal with Storm's power going out of control but the cause puts them on the trail of the captured Kitty Pryde; Kitty wakes up in Mount Haven, a city of mutants presided over by a nice, young minister, but she feels Stryker lurking behind every corner.

results.title: God Loves, Man Kills II Part 6: Pale Rider
results.description: As Kitty breaks Paul's control over the town of mutants, the truth of Mount Haven comes to light as death comes swiftly to its residents; Paul's origin is revealed and Stryker agrees to help contain the nannite plague contained within the young preacher, even though it comes at great personal sacrifice; The X-Men try to pick up the pieces and Kitty decides to move on.

results.title: Intifada Part 1: This is the Way the World Ends
results.description: Marie's family is killed on a road trip by mutants; Gambit and Storm infiltrate a briefing on the dangers of mutants that Val Cooper is holding for the President and world leaders; Bishop and Sage combat a mutant gone out of control; Later the two hook up with a still powerless Rogue and meet Sam at a Lila Cheney concert; Marie crashes the concert with bombs strapped to her chest.

results.title: The Origin of a Masked Marvel
Dreamtime Serenade
results.description: Gambit invades Vargas' stronghold and lives to tell about it; Gateway (who turns out to be Bishop's grandfather) transports Bish to the dreamtime where he gets a final message from Psylocke; The X-Men find Destiny's safehouse which turns out to belong to Rogue as part of Irene's will; Vargas has stolen Destiny's Diary that was secreted in the house.

results.title: Pride and Joy, Part 1 of 6
results.description:
At some point in their lives, all young people believe that they have something to runaway from home for? But what if it they REALLY do? 

When six young friends discover that their parents all share a deep, dark secret, the shocked teens find strength in one another and together run away from their homes and straight into the adventure of their lives. [per solicitation]

results.title: Deadline !
results.description: Sage begins to unravel the mystery of Destiny's Diary; Gambit is accused of murdering the Viceroy (the head of the Triad in Sydney); Rogue catches up to Gambit in a bar in Sydney's Chinatown where their powers are stripped and both are captured for the murder of Gow Yang (another underworld figure) by his super-powered grandson and his chief interrogator.

results.title: Paradise Lost !
results.description: Storm and Thunderbird go off to protect the Viceroy's children from underworld attacks; Gambit and Rogue escape from the Examiner; Sage begins to see herself in the Tessa persona and is captured by Shaw and Lady Mastermind.

results.title: Getting Even !
results.description: Storm and T-Bird continue to protect the Viceroy's children but one of them has powers of her own; Bishop continues his investigation of the gang war; Lady Mastermind and Shaw lock Tessa in a loop that turns her loyal to the Black King again; Rogue is also manipulated by Lady M, but Gambit gets away.

results.title: Boomerang !
results.description: Gambit takes on the Boxers; Red Lotus takes on Shaw; Rogue takes on her teammates thinking they are Vargas and crew.

results.title: Face The Music !
results.description: Red Lotus clears Gambit with the Triads by proving the Examiner was the traitor; Bishop confronts Shaw; Lifeguard dives into Sage's psyche to save her life from Lady Mastermind; Jean and Storm go shopping.

results.title: Pride and Joy, Part 2 of 6
results.description: Having discovered that their parents are all secretly super-powered villains, six young friends decide they must band together and take a stand against them. But how do you deal with finding out that people you love most in the world may be truly evil?! The emotional stakes are raised and the tables are turned in the second issue of this new ongoing series. [per solicitation]

results.title: Pride and Joy, Part 3 of 6
results.description: Surprises continue to wait around every turn for our team of teenage rebels! [per solicitation]

results.title: Pride and Joy, Part 4 of 6
results.description: When their parents finally catch up with them, Alex, Nico and the rest of the Runaways fight back! It's teenage rebellion gone wild! [per solicitation]

results.title: Pride and Joy, Part 5 of 6
results.description: The Runaways face a new threat … and it's from one of their own! [per solicitation]

results.title: Pride and Joy, Part 6 of 6
results.description: Alex, Nico and the rest of the gang make their final stand against their parents! [per solicitation]
